WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.802 --> 00:00:03.730
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i> ONE TREE HILL:

2
00:00:03.754 --> 00:00:05.087
PEYTON.

3
00:00:06.523 --> 00:00:07.656
WHO ARE YOU?

4
00:00:07.725 --> 00:00:09.258
I'M HER DAD.

5
00:00:09.326 --> 00:00:10.926
HE LOVES HIS JOB.

6
00:00:10.995 --> 00:00:13.946
IT'S JUST NOT FAIR TO
ASK HIM TO GIVE THAT UP.

7
00:00:14.014 --> 00:00:15.747
BUT I MISS HIM WHEN HE'S AWAY.

8
00:00:15.800 --> 00:00:17.266
YOU WERE RIGHT. DAN.

9
00:00:17.334 --> 00:00:19.279
WE DON'T NEED A SHRINK TO
IDENTIFY THIS FAMILY'S PROBLEM.

10
00:00:19.303 --> 00:00:20.702
YOU JUST MADE IT OBVIOUS.

11
00:00:20.771 --> 00:00:22.237
I'M NOT HIS ONLY PARENT. DEB.

12
00:00:22.306 --> 00:00:24.567
HEY. WHY DON'T YOU RIDE
WITH THE OLD MAN. NATHAN?

13
00:00:24.591 --> 00:00:25.723
COME ON. NATHAN.

14
00:00:25.792 --> 00:00:27.253
LET THE KID MAKE
UP HIS OWN MIND.

15
00:00:27.277 --> 00:00:29.111
WHAT DO YOU SAY. SON?

16
00:00:30.330 --> 00:00:32.058
I NEED TO CONNECT
MORE WITH LUCAS.

17
00:00:32.082 --> 00:00:34.116
I THOUGHT YOU GUYS
WERE ALREADY DOING THAT.

18
00:00:34.185 --> 00:00:37.402
THE MAKING-OUT THING IS GREAT
AND ALL. BUT IT ONLY GOES SO FAR.

19
00:00:37.471 --> 00:00:39.204
WHERE DO YOU GET
OFF TELLING NATHAN

20
00:00:39.273 --> 00:00:40.655
HE CAN QUIT THE TEAM?

21
00:00:40.741 --> 00:00:42.051
I DIDN'T TELL HIM HE COULD QUIT.

22
00:00:42.075 --> 00:00:43.553
HE WANTED TO TALK. WE TALKED.

23
00:00:43.577 --> 00:00:45.756
I DON'T MIND YOU PLAYING
DADDY TO ONE OF MY OFFSPRING.

24
00:00:45.780 --> 00:00:47.562
BUT LEAVE THE GOOD
ONE ALONE. WILL YA?

25
00:00:47.631 --> 00:00:51.065
YOU'RE THE FIRST REALLY
GREAT GUY THAT I'VE EVER DATED.

26
00:00:51.134 --> 00:00:53.034
AND THAT REALLY SCARES ME

27
00:00:53.103 --> 00:00:56.905
BECAUSE I NEVER GAVE
A RAT'S ASS BEFORE.

28
00:00:56.974 --> 00:00:59.374
I GIVE A RAT'S ASS
ABOUT YOU. TOO.

29
00:01:03.580 --> 00:01:04.757
I'M DONE.

30
00:01:04.781 --> 00:01:06.676
JUST THOUGHT YOU SHOULD
BE THE FIRST TO KNOW.

31
00:01:06.700 --> 00:01:07.866
ME?

32
00:01:07.935 --> 00:01:09.200
YEAH.

33
00:01:09.269 --> 00:01:11.303
YOU WANTED MY WORLD. MAN.

34
00:01:12.773 --> 00:01:14.272
IT'S ALL YOURS.

35
00:01:16.226 --> 00:01:18.493
<i>♪</i>

36
00:01:18.562 --> 00:01:20.929
<i>♪ I DON'T WANT TO BE ANYTHING ♪</i>

37
00:01:20.998 --> 00:01:24.699
<i>♪ OTHER THAN WHAT I'VE
BEEN TRYING TO BE LATELY ♪</i>

38
00:01:24.768 --> 00:01:27.135
<i>♪ ALL I HAVE TO
DO IS THINK OF ME ♪</i>

39
00:01:27.204 --> 00:01:29.337
<i>♪ AND I HAVE PEACE OF MIND ♪</i>

40
00:01:30.875 --> 00:01:33.058
<i>♪ I DON'T WANT TO BE ANYTHING ♪</i>

41
00:01:33.127 --> 00:01:37.028
<i>♪ OTHER THAN WHAT I'VE
BEEN TRYING TO BE LATELY ♪</i>

42
00:01:37.097 --> 00:01:39.664
<i>♪ ALL I HAVE TO
DO IS THINK OF ME ♪</i>

43
00:01:39.733 --> 00:01:41.867
<i>♪ AND I HAVE PEACE OF MIND ♪</i>

44
00:01:42.970 --> 00:01:45.103
<i>♪ I'M TIRED OF LOOKING 'ROUND ♪</i>

45
00:01:45.172 --> 00:01:46.854
<i>♪ WONDERING WHAT I GOTTA DO ♪</i>

46
00:01:46.923 --> 00:01:49.357
<i>♪ OR WHO I'M SUPPOSED TO BE ♪</i>

47
00:01:49.426 --> 00:01:52.060
<i>♪ I DON'T WANT TO BE ANYTHING ♪</i>

48
00:01:52.128 --> 00:01:54.629
<i>♪ OTHER THAN ME ♪</i>

49
00:01:57.367 --> 00:01:58.612
<i>HEY. HONEY.</i>

50
00:01:58.636 --> 00:01:59.668
HEY. DAD.

51
00:02:00.871 --> 00:02:02.704
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH
THE UNABOMBER LOOK?

52
00:02:02.773 --> 00:02:04.651
<i>I WAS GOING FOR GEORGE CLOONEY.</i>

53
00:02:04.675 --> 00:02:06.074
GO FURTHER.

54
00:02:07.477 --> 00:02:08.717
<i>THAT'S RIGHT. THOUGH.</i>

55
00:02:08.779 --> 00:02:10.390
<i>YOU'RE NOT USED TO
SEEING ME LIKE THIS.</i>

56
00:02:10.414 --> 00:02:12.592
<i>SEE WHEN I'M ON THE
JOB. I USUALLY LET IT GROW.</i>

57
00:02:12.616 --> 00:02:14.594
<i>THEN I SHAVE IT OFF
RIGHT BEFORE I COME HOME.</i>

58
00:02:14.618 --> 00:02:16.151
<i>KIND OF A RITUAL.</i>

59
00:02:16.219 --> 00:02:18.298
WELL. JUST MAKE SURE YOU FIND
YOUR RAZOR DAY AFTER TOMORROW.

60
00:02:18.322 --> 00:02:21.440
<i>AND AFTER THAT. I'M GONNA
BE SHAVING A LOT MORE OFTEN.</i>

61
00:02:21.508 --> 00:02:24.225
<i>HEY. BROOKE. HEY. RAKE BOY.</i>

62
00:02:24.294 --> 00:02:27.128
<i>I SEE NOBODY USES
THE DOORBELL STILL.</i>

63
00:02:27.197 --> 00:02:29.647
PAPA PEYTON. THE SCRUFFY
THING'S WORKING FOR YOU.

64
00:02:29.716 --> 00:02:31.294
<i>WHAT ARE YOU GUYS
UP TO SO EARLY?</i>

65
00:02:31.318 --> 00:02:32.851
I DON'T KNOW. PEYTON JUST...

66
00:02:32.919 --> 00:02:33.963
OH. NO. YOU KNOW WHAT?

67
00:02:33.987 --> 00:02:35.499
YOU'LL FIND OUT
WHEN YOU GET HOME.

68
00:02:35.523 --> 00:02:36.655
<i>NOT EVEN A LITTLE HINT?</i>

69
00:02:36.723 --> 00:02:38.607
MMM-MMM. NOT EVEN. I LOVE YOU.

70
00:02:38.675 --> 00:02:41.209
<i>YOU BETTER. I LOVE
YOU. TOO. HONEY.</i>

71
00:02:41.278 --> 00:02:42.360
BYE.

72
00:02:44.031 --> 00:02:46.798
SO. WHAT'S THE SURPRISE?

73
00:02:46.867 --> 00:02:49.601
I NEED YOUR HELP WITH
SOMETHING. COME ON.

74
00:02:54.008 --> 00:02:57.409
DAMN. THAT'S NICE.
THIS YOUR DAD'S?

75
00:02:57.477 --> 00:03:00.546
YEAH. HE HASN'T DRIVEN
IT LIKE IN A YEAR. THOUGH.

76
00:03:00.614 --> 00:03:02.158
DO YOU THINK YOU
CAN GET IT TO RUN?

77
00:03:02.182 --> 00:03:03.415
OF COURSE HE CAN.

78
00:03:03.483 --> 00:03:05.216
AND HE'S GONNA LOOK
GOOD DOING IT. TOO.

79
00:03:05.285 --> 00:03:08.386
IN A TIGHT LITTLE WIFE BEATER.
MAYBE SOME GREASE SMUDGES.

80
00:03:08.455 --> 00:03:11.535
AND I WAS THINKING MAYBE YOU
COULD HELP ME WASH AND WAX IT.

81
00:03:11.559 --> 00:03:13.191
I'M GLAD TO HELP.

82
00:03:13.260 --> 00:03:15.360
I JUST WANT TO DO
SOMETHING NICE FOR HIM.

83
00:03:15.429 --> 00:03:18.196
SINCE HE'S COMING HOME.

84
00:03:18.265 --> 00:03:21.433
ALL RIGHT. I'LL GO GET MY TOOLS.

85
00:03:25.956 --> 00:03:27.172
SURPRISE!

86
00:03:27.241 --> 00:03:28.951
YOU ANSWER THE DOOR
IN YOUR UNDERWEAR?

87
00:03:28.975 --> 00:03:32.105
GRANDMA. GRANDPA. WHAT
ARE YOU GUYS DOING HERE?

88
00:03:32.129 --> 00:03:35.580
ROYAL. MAY. UH. UM.
WHAT A SURPRISE.

89
00:03:35.649 --> 00:03:37.327
WELL. THANKS FOR
THE WARM WELCOME.

90
00:03:37.351 --> 00:03:39.484
I TOLD YOU THIS
AMBUSH WAS A BAD IDEA.

91
00:03:39.553 --> 00:03:41.553
HE'S DRAGGING ME TO
ANOTHER ONE OF THOSE...

92
00:03:41.621 --> 00:03:43.532
NOBODY'S DRAGGING
ANYBODY ANYWHERE.

93
00:03:43.556 --> 00:03:45.435
I TOLD HIM THAT
THE ONLY WAY I'D GO

94
00:03:45.459 --> 00:03:48.176
IS IF WE CAME BY HERE
FOR DANNY'S BIRTHDAY.

95
00:03:48.245 --> 00:03:50.962
OH. DAN'S BIRTHDAY. OF COURSE.

96
00:03:51.031 --> 00:03:52.798
YEAH.

97
00:03:52.866 --> 00:03:55.026
ARE YOU GONNA LEAVE US
STANDING OUT HERE ALL MORNING.

98
00:03:55.085 --> 00:03:56.417
FREEZING OUR ASSES OFF?

99
00:03:56.486 --> 00:03:57.897
OH. COME ON IN.

100
00:03:57.921 --> 00:03:59.587
COME ON. KISS GRAN.

101
00:03:59.656 --> 00:04:01.434
LOOKS LIKE YOU PUT
ON A FEW THERE. DEB.

102
00:04:01.458 --> 00:04:02.698
LOOKS GOOD ON YOU.

103
00:04:06.079 --> 00:04:07.679
DAN.

104
00:04:07.748 --> 00:04:09.748
YOU REMEMBERED. I'M TOUCHED.

105
00:04:09.817 --> 00:04:12.216
NO. I'M NOT HERE TO WISH
YOU A HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

106
00:04:12.285 --> 00:04:15.153
BUT YOUR PARENTS ARE.

107
00:04:15.221 --> 00:04:16.332
WHAT? YEAH.

108
00:04:16.356 --> 00:04:18.056
THEY SHOWED UP AT THE HOUSE.

109
00:04:18.124 --> 00:04:20.937
APPARENTLY YOU NEVER TOLD THEM
THAT YOU'RE NOT LIVING THERE RIGHT NOW.

110
00:04:22.028 --> 00:04:23.995
HOW'D THEY TAKE IT?

111
00:04:24.064 --> 00:04:25.864
YOU THINK I TOLD THEM?

112
00:04:25.933 --> 00:04:27.966
I'M NOT GONNA BE ON THE
RECEIVING END OF THAT.

113
00:04:28.034 --> 00:04:29.167
THAT'S YOUR JOB.

114
00:04:29.235 --> 00:04:30.747
HOW LONG ARE THEY HERE?

115
00:04:30.771 --> 00:04:32.754
JUST TONIGHT.
BUT IT GETS BETTER.

116
00:04:32.822 --> 00:04:35.957
YOUR MOTHER IS COOKING
YOU A BIG BIRTHDAY DINNER.

117
00:04:36.026 --> 00:04:37.726
OH. PERFECT.

118
00:04:37.794 --> 00:04:39.634
ALL RIGHT. SO WHAT
ARE WE GONNA DO?

119
00:04:39.679 --> 00:04:41.579
WE ARE NOT GOING TO DO ANYTHING.

120
00:04:41.648 --> 00:04:44.182
YOU ARE GOING TO GO
TO THE HOUSE RIGHT NOW.

121
00:04:44.251 --> 00:04:45.850
AND TELL THEM WE'RE SEPARATED.

122
00:04:45.919 --> 00:04:47.430
NO. WE'RE DOING THE COUNSELING.

123
00:04:47.454 --> 00:04:50.500
WE'RE GONNA WORK THIS THING OUT.
RIGHT? ISN'T THAT THE WHOLE POINT?

124
00:04:50.524 --> 00:04:51.524
IT IS.

125
00:04:51.558 --> 00:04:53.419
WELL. YOU KNOW HOW THEY ARE.

126
00:04:53.443 --> 00:04:55.705
DO YOU REALLY WANT THEM WEIGHING
IN ON THE STATE OF OUR MARRIAGE?

127
00:04:55.729 --> 00:04:58.741
DO YOU REMEMBER WHEN WE TOLD THEM
WE WEREN'T GONNA HAVE ANY MORE KIDS?

128
00:04:58.765 --> 00:05:00.543
HOW MANY TIMES
DID MY DAD CALL YOU?

129
00:05:00.567 --> 00:05:03.379
AND NOW YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE
THE OPTION OF HANGING UP ON HIM.

130
00:05:03.403 --> 00:05:05.153
GO ON. DAN. JUST SAY IT.

131
00:05:05.222 --> 00:05:06.966
WE GO THROUGH
THE MOTIONS TONIGHT.

132
00:05:06.990 --> 00:05:08.801
GET IT OVER WITH. SEND
THEM ON THEIR WAY.

133
00:05:08.825 --> 00:05:11.293
GO BACK TO WORKING ON US.

134
00:05:11.361 --> 00:05:14.029
BESIDES. IT MIGHT DO SOME GOOD

135
00:05:14.097 --> 00:05:17.377
TO TRY AND REMEMBER WHAT
IT'S LIKE TO BE A NORMAL FAMILY.

136
00:05:19.136 --> 00:05:22.104
FINE. JUST FOR TONIGHT.

137
00:05:22.172 --> 00:05:23.805
JUST FOR TONIGHT.

138
00:05:25.000 --> 00:05:31.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

139
00:05:33.683 --> 00:05:36.123
GOOD MORNING. SIR.
TABLE OR COUNTER?

140
00:05:36.153 --> 00:05:38.719
AH. ACTUALLY. I'M
LOOKING FOR KAREN.

141
00:05:38.788 --> 00:05:41.973
OH. NO. SHE'S IN ITALY
RIGHT NOW. COOKING SCHOOL.

142
00:05:42.942 --> 00:05:44.775
GOOD FOR HER.

143
00:05:44.844 --> 00:05:46.844
HOW'S THAT BOY OF HERS DOING?

144
00:05:46.913 --> 00:05:49.047
UH. LUCAS IS GREAT.

145
00:05:49.115 --> 00:05:50.743
SHE CALLS IN EVERY
ONCE IN A WHILE.

146
00:05:50.767 --> 00:05:52.779
DO YOU WANT ME
TO LEAVE A MESSAGE?

147
00:05:52.803 --> 00:05:54.836
NO. THAT'S ALL RIGHT.
I'LL JUST. UH. CATCH HER

148
00:05:54.905 --> 00:05:56.305
THE NEXT TIME I'M
PASSING THROUGH.

149
00:05:56.372 --> 00:05:57.505
OK.

150
00:05:57.573 --> 00:06:00.592
CAN I TELL HER WHO
STOPPED BY. MR...

151
00:06:00.661 --> 00:06:02.393
JUST AN OLD FRIEND.

152
00:06:16.059 --> 00:06:18.627
WELL. IT'S NOT THE BATTERY.

153
00:06:18.695 --> 00:06:20.194
IT'S PROBABLY THE STARTER.

154
00:06:20.263 --> 00:06:22.914
WELL. YOU CAN FIX THAT. RIGHT?

155
00:06:22.983 --> 00:06:25.266
YEAH. IT SHOULDN'T BE A PROBLEM.

156
00:06:27.537 --> 00:06:28.970
OH. IT'S AN AMAZING CAR.

157
00:06:29.039 --> 00:06:30.071
HMM.

158
00:06:30.140 --> 00:06:31.673
IT'S AN AMAZING GUY.

159
00:06:31.742 --> 00:06:33.074
OH. MMM.

160
00:06:34.477 --> 00:06:36.222
IS THAT WHAT YOU
GOT ME THIS THING FOR?

161
00:06:36.246 --> 00:06:37.262
UH-HUH.

162
00:06:37.330 --> 00:06:38.370
YEAH.

163
00:06:42.268 --> 00:06:44.986
I WAS JUST GETTING STARTED.

164
00:06:45.055 --> 00:06:46.687
SADLY. SO WAS I.

165
00:06:48.525 --> 00:06:50.108
WHAT'S WRONG?

166
00:06:50.177 --> 00:06:52.927
I'M JUST WORRIED ABOUT MY DAD.

167
00:06:52.996 --> 00:06:54.762
ALL RIGHT. I JUST
CHECKED ONLINE.

168
00:06:54.831 --> 00:06:57.532
AND NOW THEY'RE SAYING
IT'S A CATEGORY 3 HURRICANE.

169
00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:59.778
ALL RIGHT AND YOU ALREADY
CHECKED THE WEBCAM. RIGHT?

170
00:06:59.802 --> 00:07:00.846
YEAH. IT'S OUT.

171
00:07:00.870 --> 00:07:02.303
OR MAYBE HE TURNED IT OFF.

172
00:07:02.372 --> 00:07:04.372
OR THE STORM DID IT FOR HIM.

173
00:07:04.441 --> 00:07:06.819
YEAH. BUT STORMS KNOCK THAT
KIND OF THING OUT ALL THE TIME. RIGHT?

174
00:07:06.843 --> 00:07:08.554
ANYWAY. AREN'T
DREDGING BOATS HUGE?

175
00:07:08.578 --> 00:07:10.123
HE WOULDN'T BE ON
THE DREDGING BOAT.

176
00:07:10.147 --> 00:07:12.258
RIGHT NOW. IF THERE'S A
STORM HEADED THIS WAY.

177
00:07:12.282 --> 00:07:14.293
HE'D BE ON THIS
LITTLE. TINY TRANSPORT

178
00:07:14.317 --> 00:07:16.462
HEADED BACK TO SHORE.
AND THAT'S WHAT WORRIES ME.

179
00:07:16.486 --> 00:07:19.620
OK. PEYTON. JUST STOP. DON'T
DO THIS TO YOURSELF. ALL RIGHT?

180
00:07:19.689 --> 00:07:21.167
JUST BECAUSE HE
HASN'T CHECKED IN

181
00:07:21.191 --> 00:07:22.890
DOESN'T MEAN
SOMETHING'S HAPPENED.

182
00:07:22.959 --> 00:07:25.360
IT DOESN'T MEAN
IT HASN'T. EITHER.

183
00:07:30.934 --> 00:07:35.236
SO. THIS. UH. DINNER THING IS
GONNA BE PRETTY BAD. HUH?

184
00:07:35.305 --> 00:07:37.072
A MASSACRE.

185
00:07:37.140 --> 00:07:38.707
MY GRANDMA'S OK.

186
00:07:38.775 --> 00:07:41.876
IT'S JUST MY GRAMP
IS PRETTY INTENSE.

187
00:07:41.945 --> 00:07:43.678
YOU'VE MET MY DAD.

188
00:07:43.747 --> 00:07:45.246
JUST IMAGINE WHERE
HE COMES FROM.

189
00:07:45.315 --> 00:07:46.392
SCARY.

190
00:07:46.416 --> 00:07:47.515
YEAH.

191
00:07:48.318 --> 00:07:49.918
YOU SHOULD COME TONIGHT.

192
00:07:49.986 --> 00:07:51.386
MAYBE IT'LL MAKE
EVERYBODY BEHAVE.

193
00:07:52.923 --> 00:07:55.056
I'LL COME IF YOU WANT ME TO.

194
00:07:55.125 --> 00:07:56.657
NO. I WASN'T SERIOUS.

195
00:07:56.727 --> 00:07:58.193
I WOULDN'T PUT YOU THROUGH THAT.

196
00:07:58.261 --> 00:08:01.896
WELL. I MEAN. IF YOU'RE ASKING.
OF COURSE. MY ANSWER'S YES.

197
00:08:02.599 --> 00:08:04.999
WELL. THEN I'M ASKING.

198
00:08:05.068 --> 00:08:06.400
WELL. THEN I'M COMING.

199
00:08:08.421 --> 00:08:09.654
LET ME GET THIS RIGHT.

200
00:08:09.723 --> 00:08:12.557
CHARCOAL FINISH.
CUSTOM-LEATHER PACKAGE.

201
00:08:12.626 --> 00:08:14.626
WHAT YOU WANT IS A
CHAMPAGNE INTERIOR.

202
00:08:14.695 --> 00:08:16.305
I'M HERE TO SEE THE MANAGER.

203
00:08:16.329 --> 00:08:18.062
EXCUSE ME.

204
00:08:18.131 --> 00:08:20.360
HEY. FELLA. YOU OUGHT TO KNOW
WHO YOU'RE DOING BUSINESS WITH.

205
00:08:20.384 --> 00:08:21.800
IS THERE A PROBLEM?

206
00:08:21.868 --> 00:08:24.781
NO. YOU'RE BUYING FROM DAN
SCOTT. BASKETBALL LEGEND.

207
00:08:24.805 --> 00:08:27.655
STILL HOLDS THE ALL-TIME
SCORING RECORD FOR TREE HILL.

208
00:08:27.724 --> 00:08:29.435
MADE ALL-STATE HIS SENIOR YEAR.

209
00:08:29.459 --> 00:08:30.408
NO KIDDING?

210
00:08:30.476 --> 00:08:31.409
NO KIDDING.

211
00:08:31.477 --> 00:08:32.477
MY DAD.

212
00:08:32.512 --> 00:08:33.512
I FIGURED.

213
00:08:33.547 --> 00:08:35.430
YOU PLAY COLLEGE. TOO?

214
00:08:35.498 --> 00:08:37.327
WOULD HAVE. BUT HE BLEW HIS
KNEE OUT IN HIS FRESHMAN YEAR.

215
00:08:37.351 --> 00:08:39.428
HE GOT ROBBED. WOULD
HAVE BEEN ONE OF THE GREATS.

216
00:08:39.452 --> 00:08:41.231
DAD. MR. MILLER'S
REALLY NOT INTERESTED.

217
00:08:41.255 --> 00:08:43.933
I'LL TEL YOU WHAT. MEET ME IN
MY OFFICE. OK? I'LL BE RIGHT IN.

218
00:08:43.957 --> 00:08:47.224
CHAMPAGNE INTERIOR.
RIGHT? ALL RIGHT.

219
00:08:47.293 --> 00:08:49.338
WHAT? SOMEBODY'S
GOT TO BRAG ON YOU.

220
00:08:49.362 --> 00:08:52.024
AND YOU'RE NOT GONNA CLOSE THAT
SALE WITHOUT YOUR OLD MAN'S HELP.

221
00:08:52.048 --> 00:08:53.176
YOU KNOW THAT. DON'T YOU?

222
00:08:53.200 --> 00:08:55.033
YOU ALWAYS WERE
MY BIGGEST PROMOTER.

223
00:08:55.102 --> 00:08:57.468
I GUESS.

224
00:08:57.537 --> 00:08:59.938
HEY. STILL IN SHAPE.
GOOD FOR YOU.

225
00:09:05.578 --> 00:09:07.795
OH. YOU'RE HOME.
LISTEN. I CALLED NATHAN.

226
00:09:07.864 --> 00:09:10.243
I TOLD HIM NOT TO TELL DAD
HE'S NOT GOING TO PRACTICE.

227
00:09:10.267 --> 00:09:11.699
YOU MEAN THAT HE QUIT THE TEAM?

228
00:09:11.768 --> 00:09:13.234
YOU KNOW WHAT I MEAN.

229
00:09:13.303 --> 00:09:15.770
I ALSO TOLD KEITH TO
AVOID THE SUBJECT.

230
00:09:15.839 --> 00:09:18.206
ANY OTHER LIES I SHOULD
REMEMBER TO TELL?

231
00:09:18.275 --> 00:09:20.741
I'M TRYING TO PROTECT OUR
SON FROM MY FATHER. OK?

232
00:09:20.810 --> 00:09:22.978
YOU DON'T EVEN SEE
THE IRONY. DO YOU?

233
00:09:23.046 --> 00:09:25.313
MOM. YOU LOOK BEAUTIFUL AS EVER.

234
00:09:25.382 --> 00:09:27.131
GOD BLESS YOU FOR A LIAR.

235
00:09:27.200 --> 00:09:29.178
I COMPLIMENT YOU.
YOU CALL ME A LIAR.

236
00:09:29.202 --> 00:09:30.368
YOU LOOK TIRED.

237
00:09:30.437 --> 00:09:31.836
HEY. SON. WHAT'S THE DEAL?

238
00:09:31.904 --> 00:09:33.144
NO MORE CHARLOTTE HORNETS?

239
00:09:33.172 --> 00:09:34.417
YEAH. NEW ORLEANS CAN HAVE THEM.

240
00:09:34.441 --> 00:09:36.107
YOU THINK THEY HAVE
A PLAYOFFS HOPE?

241
00:09:36.175 --> 00:09:37.308
NO. NO.

242
00:09:37.377 --> 00:09:38.509
NO SPORTS TALK.

243
00:09:38.578 --> 00:09:40.256
OH. COME ON.

244
00:09:40.280 --> 00:09:41.412
YES. MA'AM.

245
00:09:42.549 --> 00:09:43.914
OH.

246
00:09:43.983 --> 00:09:45.428
I JUST BECAME HEAD
OF THE TABLE. DIDN'T I?

247
00:09:45.452 --> 00:09:46.662
KEITH. MOM.

248
00:09:46.686 --> 00:09:48.786
HMM. MMM. YOU LOOK GREAT.

249
00:09:48.855 --> 00:09:51.389
WELL. LOOK WHAT
THE CAT DRAGGED IN.

250
00:09:51.458 --> 00:09:53.001
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU. TOO. DAD.

251
00:09:53.025 --> 00:09:54.626
UH-HUH.

252
00:09:54.694 --> 00:09:56.361
HAPPY BIRTHDAY. DANNY.

253
00:09:56.429 --> 00:09:58.396
YEAH. THANKS.

254
00:09:58.465 --> 00:10:02.166
COME ON. HAVE A SEAT.
DINNER IS ALMOST READY.

255
00:10:02.235 --> 00:10:04.179
DANNY. WILL YOU POUR
SOME WINE. PLEASE?

256
00:10:04.203 --> 00:10:05.314
I'M ON IT.

257
00:10:05.338 --> 00:10:06.654
AMEN TO THAT.

258
00:10:06.723 --> 00:10:08.668
UM. LISTEN. MOM. WE'RE GONNA
NEED ANOTHER PLACE SETTING.

259
00:10:08.692 --> 00:10:10.558
I. UH. I INVITED A GUEST.

260
00:10:10.627 --> 00:10:12.794
A DATE? OH. MY GOODNESS.

261
00:10:12.863 --> 00:10:15.307
WELL. YOU GET THAT CHAIR
OVER THERE AND I WILL...

262
00:10:15.331 --> 00:10:17.499
GRANDPA. GRANDMA. THIS IS HALEY.

263
00:10:17.567 --> 00:10:20.118
OH. HALEY. NICE TO MEET YOU.

264
00:10:20.186 --> 00:10:22.053
NICE TO MEET YOU. TOO.

265
00:10:25.642 --> 00:10:28.721
WELL. NATHAN. YOU'RE LOOKING MORE
AND MORE LIKE YOUR OLD MAN EVERY DAY.

266
00:10:28.745 --> 00:10:31.123
WE ALL KNOW WHERE HE GETS
HIS GOOD LOOKS. DON'T WE?

267
00:10:31.147 --> 00:10:32.280
OH. COME ON IN.

268
00:10:32.348 --> 00:10:33.793
YOU SIT RIGHT HERE
NEXT TO ME. HONEY.

269
00:10:33.817 --> 00:10:34.927
THANK YOU.

270
00:10:34.951 --> 00:10:36.050
I'LL GET IT.

271
00:10:36.119 --> 00:10:37.597
EVERYTHING LOOKS SO NICE.

272
00:10:37.621 --> 00:10:39.821
OH. MY GOODNESS. WHITEY.

273
00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:41.367
GOOD EVENING. EVERYBODY.

274
00:10:41.391 --> 00:10:42.468
GOOD TO SEE YOU.

275
00:10:42.492 --> 00:10:44.125
SORRY I'M LATE.

276
00:10:44.194 --> 00:10:45.242
HEY. ROYAL...

277
00:10:45.312 --> 00:10:46.627
GLAD YOU CAME?

278
00:10:46.696 --> 00:10:47.895
YEAH.

279
00:10:52.902 --> 00:10:54.869
ALL RIGHT. TRY IT AGAIN.

280
00:10:57.207 --> 00:10:58.573
WE GOT POWER.

281
00:10:59.342 --> 00:11:01.376
PEYTON. COME CHECK IT OUT.

282
00:11:04.814 --> 00:11:06.181
WHAT IS IT?

283
00:11:07.484 --> 00:11:09.451
I JUST GOT A PHONE CALL.

284
00:11:10.220 --> 00:11:11.886
UM. IT'S THE STORM.

285
00:11:11.955 --> 00:11:14.822
MY DAD'S TRANSPORT IS MISSING.

286
00:11:14.891 --> 00:11:16.891
THERE WERE 3 GUYS ON IT.

287
00:11:16.960 --> 00:11:18.926
THEY RECOVERED A BODY.

288
00:11:18.995 --> 00:11:20.912
WHAT DID THEY TELL YOU?

289
00:11:22.282 --> 00:11:24.482
I HAVE TO GO SEE IF IT'S HIM.

290
00:11:33.592 --> 00:11:36.193
YOU SURE YOU SHOULDN'T
CALL YOUR GRANDMOTHER?

291
00:11:36.262 --> 00:11:37.795
NO. SHE'D FREAK OUT.

292
00:11:37.864 --> 00:11:39.908
I'D RATHER NOT UPSET HER.
BESIDES. IT'S NOT GONNA BE MY DAD.

293
00:11:39.932 --> 00:11:41.198
OF COURSE IT'S NOT.

294
00:11:41.267 --> 00:11:42.945
LET'S GO AHEAD AND
GET THIS OVER WITH.

295
00:11:42.969 --> 00:11:44.769
WE HAVE A 4-HOUR
DRIVE AHEAD OF US.

296
00:11:44.838 --> 00:11:47.538
A 4-HOUR DRIVE INTO A STORM?

297
00:11:47.607 --> 00:11:49.118
WELL. THE STORM'S
PASSING THROUGH.

298
00:11:49.142 --> 00:11:51.070
BY THE TIME WE GET
THERE. IT SHOULD BE GONE.

299
00:11:51.094 --> 00:11:53.110
OK. WAIT A SECOND.

300
00:11:53.179 --> 00:11:55.524
SHOULDN'T SOMEBODY STAY HERE BY
THE PHONE IN CASE YOUR DAD CALLS?

301
00:11:55.548 --> 00:11:57.632
I WILL. YOU GO WITH PEYTON.

302
00:11:57.701 --> 00:11:58.649
YOU SURE?

303
00:11:58.719 --> 00:12:00.484
YEAH.

304
00:12:00.553 --> 00:12:02.631
LUCAS. YOU'RE GOOD IN A CRISIS.
NOT THAT THERE'S GONNA BE ONE.

305
00:12:02.655 --> 00:12:04.489
BUT I WOULD PROBABLY
END UP FALLING APART.

306
00:12:04.558 --> 00:12:07.208
AND YOU'D END UP TAKING CARE
OF ME. WHICH IS NOT THE POINT.

307
00:12:07.276 --> 00:12:08.409
SO...

308
00:12:09.912 --> 00:12:12.580
I LOVE YOU. IT'S GONNA BE OK.

309
00:12:14.016 --> 00:12:15.616
YOU'RE THE BEST.

310
00:12:19.322 --> 00:12:21.922
I'LL CALL YOU GUYS
IF I HEAR ANYTHING.

311
00:12:23.543 --> 00:12:25.659
HOW'S THE TEAM DOING
THIS YEAR. WHITEY?

312
00:12:25.728 --> 00:12:28.279
OH. WE'RE STILL
UNDEFEATED. ACTUALLY.

313
00:12:29.482 --> 00:12:31.516
DAD. YOU STILL ROOTING
FOR MAGIC THESE DAYS?

314
00:12:33.085 --> 00:12:36.654
PLEASE. NO TALK OF SPORTS
UNTIL AFTER DINNER. OK?

315
00:12:36.723 --> 00:12:39.907
GOOD IDEA. MOM. I'M SORRY.

316
00:12:39.976 --> 00:12:42.677
WELL. NATHAN. WHAT ARE
YOU AVERAGING THESE DAYS?

317
00:12:42.745 --> 00:12:44.945
YOU KNOW. YOUR DAD
HAD 27 AND A HALF A GAME.

318
00:12:45.014 --> 00:12:46.047
YOU BEAT THAT YET?

319
00:12:46.115 --> 00:12:47.348
ROYAL. WE JUST...

320
00:12:47.417 --> 00:12:49.834
I'M ASKING THE BOY
A QUESTION. MAY.

321
00:12:52.271 --> 00:12:53.471
UH.

322
00:12:53.539 --> 00:12:56.019
MAYBE YOU SHOULD
ASK THE OLD MAN.

323
00:12:59.229 --> 00:13:01.423
UH. 24 POINTS A
GAME. I THINK. ISN'T IT?

324
00:13:01.447 --> 00:13:02.825
SO. 24 A GAME. HUH?

325
00:13:02.849 --> 00:13:04.716
YOU KNOW. YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO GET THAT UP

326
00:13:04.784 --> 00:13:06.417
IF YOU'RE GONNA
BEAT THE OLD MAN.

327
00:13:06.486 --> 00:13:08.119
YEAH. YOUR DAD'S STAR

328
00:13:08.187 --> 00:13:10.438
WOULD HAVE RISEN THROUGH
THE ROOF AT CAROLINA

329
00:13:10.507 --> 00:13:13.841
IF IT HADN'T BEEN FOR THAT DAMN
KNEE OF HIS. HOW ARE YOUR KNEES?

330
00:13:13.910 --> 00:13:14.987
NO WORRIES.

331
00:13:15.011 --> 00:13:16.744
MMM. HE'S GOT GREAT KNEES.

332
00:13:19.749 --> 00:13:20.915
UH-HUH.

333
00:13:20.983 --> 00:13:22.133
OF COURSE. NOW.

334
00:13:22.202 --> 00:13:24.018
DANNY TAKES AFTER
HIS OLD MAN. YOU KNOW?

335
00:13:24.087 --> 00:13:26.654
NEVER LET ADVERSITY STOP HIM.

336
00:13:26.723 --> 00:13:30.091
TOO BAD KEITH TAKES AFTER
HIS MOTHER'S SIDE OF THE FAMILY.

337
00:13:30.159 --> 00:13:31.642
LUCKY FOR HIM.

338
00:13:31.711 --> 00:13:34.745
I'D DRINK TO THAT. BUT
I GOT TO GET A REFILL.

339
00:13:35.682 --> 00:13:36.881
YEAH.

340
00:13:36.950 --> 00:13:38.716
WELL. I SHOULD SEE
ABOUT THE CAKE.

341
00:13:38.785 --> 00:13:40.362
MMM. I'LL GO DO
THAT. MRS. SCOTT.

342
00:13:40.386 --> 00:13:41.786
WANT TO COME HELP?

343
00:13:41.855 --> 00:13:44.055
YEAH. YEAH. THE CAKE. RIGHT.

344
00:13:49.462 --> 00:13:51.295
I WARNED YOU IT WAS
GONNA BE INTENSE.

345
00:13:51.364 --> 00:13:54.132
OH. INSANE IS MORE LIKE IT.

346
00:13:54.200 --> 00:13:55.833
YOU KNOW. THERE'S
A DOOR RIGHT THERE.

347
00:13:55.902 --> 00:13:57.501
WE COULD SNEAK OUT.

348
00:13:57.570 --> 00:13:58.770
NOBODY WOULD EVEN NOTICE.

349
00:13:58.838 --> 00:14:00.404
MMM. TEMPTING.

350
00:14:01.340 --> 00:14:03.141
UM.

351
00:14:03.209 --> 00:14:05.838
SO. HOW OFTEN DO YOUR
GRANDPARENTS COME INTO TOWN?

352
00:14:05.862 --> 00:14:08.012
A COUPLE TIMES A YEAR. WHY?

353
00:14:09.883 --> 00:14:11.566
HALEY. YOU'VE GOT THAT LOOK.

354
00:14:11.634 --> 00:14:13.200
WHAT LOOK?

355
00:14:13.269 --> 00:14:15.114
THE LOOK YOU GIVE WHEN
YOU WANNA TELL ME SOMETHING

356
00:14:15.138 --> 00:14:16.620
BUT YOU DON'T
REALLY WANNA TELL ME.

357
00:14:16.690 --> 00:14:18.756
NO. I DON'T. AND YOU
SHOULDN'T KNOW THAT LOOK YET.

358
00:14:18.825 --> 00:14:21.025
WHAT IS IT?

359
00:14:21.094 --> 00:14:25.462
YOUR GRANDFATHER CAME BY THE
CAFE TODAY AND HE ASKED FOR KAREN.

360
00:14:25.531 --> 00:14:26.531
HE DID?

361
00:14:26.566 --> 00:14:27.982
YEAH.

362
00:14:28.051 --> 00:14:31.047
I JUST GOT THE KIND OF FEELING
LIKE THEY'VE BEEN KEEPING IN TOUCH.

363
00:14:31.071 --> 00:14:32.536
DOES LUCAS KNOW HIM?

364
00:14:32.605 --> 00:14:34.605
NO. THEY'VE NEVER EVEN MET.

365
00:14:34.674 --> 00:14:36.919
BUT YOUR GRANDFATHER
ASKED ABOUT HIM.

366
00:14:36.943 --> 00:14:38.759
THAT DOESN'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

367
00:14:38.828 --> 00:14:41.045
MY GRANDPA ACTS LIKE MY
DAD'S THE SECOND COMING.

368
00:14:41.114 --> 00:14:42.647
WHY WOULD HE VISIT KAREN?

369
00:14:42.716 --> 00:14:46.095
I DON'T KNOW. I DON'T WANT TO
START ANYTHING. I'M JUST TELLING YOU.

370
00:14:46.119 --> 00:14:48.469
YOU KNOW WHAT? MY
FAMILY'S SO SCREWED UP.

371
00:14:48.538 --> 00:14:50.538
NOTHING NEW WOULD MAKE
A DIFFERENCE RIGHT NOW.

372
00:14:50.607 --> 00:14:53.807
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

373
00:14:53.876 --> 00:14:55.756
<i>♪</i>

374
00:14:55.811 --> 00:14:59.113
<i>♪ I'VE BEEN RIDING SLOWLY
OUT INTO THE SALTY EVENINGS ♪</i>

375
00:14:59.182 --> 00:15:00.781
YOU WARM ENOUGH?

376
00:15:00.850 --> 00:15:02.250
I'M OK.

377
00:15:02.318 --> 00:15:05.253
I SHOULD PROBABLY GET THE
HEATER FIXED IN HERE. HUH?

378
00:15:05.321 --> 00:15:07.466
I COULD HAVE KEITH TAKE
A LOOK AT IT FOR YOU.

379
00:15:07.490 --> 00:15:09.690
HE'S REALLY GOOD AT THAT STUFF.

380
00:15:09.759 --> 00:15:12.226
<i>♪ AND MY FEVER CLIMBS
THE MORE I ROLL ♪</i>

381
00:15:12.295 --> 00:15:14.573
YOU WANT ME TO STOP
AND GET SOME COFFEE?

382
00:15:14.597 --> 00:15:16.930
I'M FINE. THANKS.

383
00:15:16.999 --> 00:15:18.677
<i>♪ WITH ALL THE
COVER IN THE WORLD ♪</i>

384
00:15:18.701 --> 00:15:21.802
<i>♪ MY SKIN STILL SHOWS ♪</i>

385
00:15:21.871 --> 00:15:24.272
THANKS FOR DOING
THIS FOR ME. LUKE.

386
00:15:25.375 --> 00:15:27.875
THAT'S WHAT FRIENDS
ARE FOR. RIGHT?

387
00:15:28.511 --> 00:15:29.644
YEAH.

388
00:15:38.604 --> 00:15:39.871
NOW WHAT?

389
00:15:46.679 --> 00:15:47.812
WHAT'S GOING ON?

390
00:15:47.881 --> 00:15:49.558
THE BRIDGE IS UP
BECAUSE OF THE STORM.

391
00:15:49.582 --> 00:15:51.182
IT'LL BE OPEN IN THE MORNING.

392
00:15:51.251 --> 00:15:52.516
WE HAVE AN EMERGENCY.

393
00:15:52.585 --> 00:15:53.996
WE HAVE TO GET
ACROSS THE BRIDGE.

394
00:15:54.020 --> 00:15:56.387
I'M SORRY. MISS.
BUT. UH. IT'S NOT SAFE.

395
00:15:56.455 --> 00:15:58.656
OK. UM. IS THERE
ANOTHER WAY THROUGH?

396
00:15:58.724 --> 00:16:01.893
ONLY THE FERRIES. BUT. UH. THE CHANNEL'S
TOO ROUGH. SO THEY'RE NOT RUNNING.

397
00:16:01.961 --> 00:16:03.661
WHAT ARE WE SUPPOSED TO DO?

398
00:16:03.729 --> 00:16:07.398
HOPEFULLY. WE'LL BE ABLE TO LOWER THE BRIDGE IN THE MORNING.
- 00 A.M.

399
00:16:07.466 --> 00:16:09.400
THERE'S A MOTEL
RIGHT DOWN THE ROAD.

400
00:16:09.468 --> 00:16:13.104
MIGHT WANT TO GRAB YOURSELF
A ROOM BEFORE THEY'RE ALL GONE.

401
00:16:23.966 --> 00:16:26.206
THERE YOU GO.

402
00:16:27.970 --> 00:16:30.003
SO. NATE. HOW'S
YOUR GAME THIS YEAR?

403
00:16:30.072 --> 00:16:31.367
HERE WE GO AGAIN.

404
00:16:31.391 --> 00:16:33.224
JUST COVER YOUR EARS. MAY.

405
00:16:33.293 --> 00:16:35.855
I JUST WANT TO KNOW HOW MY
GRANDSON'S DOING ON THE TEAM.

406
00:16:35.879 --> 00:16:37.211
I ALREADY TOLD YOU. DAD.

407
00:16:37.280 --> 00:16:39.191
NO. YOU DIDN'T. YOU
DIDN'T TELL ME JACK.

408
00:16:39.215 --> 00:16:42.817
EVERY TIME I MENTION IT. YOU
CHANGE THE DAMN SUBJECT.

409
00:16:42.885 --> 00:16:46.086
WILL SOMEBODY AROUND
HERE TELL ME WHAT'S GOING ON?

410
00:16:46.923 --> 00:16:48.188
NATHAN?

411
00:16:49.592 --> 00:16:51.793
WHITEY? ANYBODY?

412
00:16:51.861 --> 00:16:54.611
NATHAN. I THINK YOU
BETTER TAKE THIS ONE.

413
00:16:58.400 --> 00:17:00.251
I QUIT THE TEAM. ALL RIGHT?

414
00:17:00.319 --> 00:17:02.531
YOU QUITE THE... WHAT DO
YOU MEAN YOU QUIT THE TEAM?

415
00:17:02.555 --> 00:17:03.937
HE DIDN'T QUIT THE TEAM. DAD.

416
00:17:04.006 --> 00:17:05.373
HE'S JUST TAKING SOME TIME OFF.

417
00:17:05.441 --> 00:17:08.759
NO. HE'S NOT. PLEASE
STOP LYING. DAN.

418
00:17:08.828 --> 00:17:10.628
WERE YOU EVER
GONNA TELL ME THIS?

419
00:17:10.697 --> 00:17:12.708
I MEAN. THAT'S A HELL OF A
THING TO KEEP TO YOURSELF.

420
00:17:12.732 --> 00:17:13.972
YEAH. YOU'RE ONE TO TALK.

421
00:17:14.033 --> 00:17:15.265
WHAT'S THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

422
00:17:15.334 --> 00:17:18.052
I KNOW YOU VISIT KAREN
AT THE CAFE. ALL RIGHT?

423
00:17:18.121 --> 00:17:19.264
WHAT'S THAT ABOUT?

424
00:17:19.288 --> 00:17:21.188
THAT'S NONE OF
YOUR DAMN BUSINESS.

425
00:17:21.257 --> 00:17:22.990
I GUESS SOMEBODY'S
GOT A BIG MOUTH.

426
00:17:23.059 --> 00:17:24.358
WILL YOU SHUT UP. GRANDPA?

427
00:17:24.426 --> 00:17:25.805
DON'T YOU TALK TO ME LIKE THAT!

428
00:17:25.829 --> 00:17:27.345
BACK OFF. ROYAL.

429
00:17:27.413 --> 00:17:29.046
I'VE HAD ENOUGH OF YOUR CRAP.

430
00:17:29.115 --> 00:17:31.416
NATHAN IS NOT THE PROBLEM.

431
00:17:31.484 --> 00:17:33.717
WOULD SOMEONE PLEASE EXPLAIN?

432
00:17:40.292 --> 00:17:44.095
DAN HAS BEEN RIDING NATHAN FOR THE
PAST 6 YEARS ABOUT THAT DAMN GAME.

433
00:17:44.163 --> 00:17:45.763
DEB. STOP.

434
00:17:45.832 --> 00:17:48.699
RIDING HIM SO HARD THAT NATHAN
TOOK DRUGS SO HE COULD MEASURE UP.

435
00:17:48.768 --> 00:17:50.101
DRUGS?

436
00:17:50.169 --> 00:17:52.252
UNTIL HE HAD TO BE
RUSHED TO THE HOSPITAL.

437
00:17:52.321 --> 00:17:55.785
HE COULD HAVE DIED BECAUSE
OF THIS... THIS INSANE PRESSURE

438
00:17:55.809 --> 00:17:58.642
TO PUT A BALL THROUGH A HOOP.

439
00:17:58.711 --> 00:18:01.562
BUT NONE OF THAT IS
MY SON'S FAULT. ROYAL.

440
00:18:02.365 --> 00:18:03.965
IT'S YOUR SON'S.

441
00:18:07.403 --> 00:18:10.303
DANNY. YOU OF ALL PEOPLE?

442
00:18:11.173 --> 00:18:13.306
HOW DARE YOU.

443
00:18:13.375 --> 00:18:15.142
YOU KNOW HOW MUCH YOU HATED IT

444
00:18:15.210 --> 00:18:17.344
WHEN YOUR DADDY
BULLIED YOU TO BE BETTER.

445
00:18:17.413 --> 00:18:20.064
I NEVER BULLIED HIM!

446
00:18:20.132 --> 00:18:23.300
AND WHEN YOU WANTED A
WAY OUT. I GAVE YOU ONE.

447
00:18:23.353 --> 00:18:25.919
ALL THESE YEARS.
I PROTECTED YOU.

448
00:18:25.988 --> 00:18:27.621
I LIED FOR YOU.

449
00:18:27.690 --> 00:18:30.474
AND NOW YOU'RE DOING THE
SAME THING TO YOUR SON?

450
00:18:30.542 --> 00:18:32.287
WHAT LIE? WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

451
00:18:32.311 --> 00:18:34.979
IN COLLEGE. HIS KNEE INJURY...

452
00:18:35.898 --> 00:18:37.698
IT WASN'T PERMANENT.

453
00:18:39.301 --> 00:18:41.868
DANNY QUIT. AND I HELPED HIM.

454
00:18:51.731 --> 00:18:53.130
WHAT DO YOU MEAN HE QUIT?

455
00:18:53.198 --> 00:18:54.532
IT'S NOT LIKE THAT. DAD.

456
00:18:54.600 --> 00:18:56.967
OH. STOP IT. DAN. IT'S
TIME THE TRUTH CAME OUT.

457
00:18:57.036 --> 00:18:59.848
WILL SOMEBODY TELL ME WHAT
IN THE HELL IS GOING ON HERE?

458
00:18:59.872 --> 00:19:03.474
YOU WERE ON THE ROAD
WHEN DANNY HURT HIS KNEE.

459
00:19:03.543 --> 00:19:05.275
SO WE LIED.

460
00:19:05.344 --> 00:19:07.878
YOU TOLD ME IT WAS A
DEGENERATIVE KNEE CONDITION.

461
00:19:07.947 --> 00:19:09.279
IT WAS DAD...

462
00:19:09.348 --> 00:19:12.316
YOU LOOKED ME IN THE
EYE. AND YOU TOLD ME THAT.

463
00:19:13.485 --> 00:19:15.102
DON'T YOU SEE. ROYAL?

464
00:19:15.171 --> 00:19:18.940
HE WAS NEVER GONNA BE THE
STAR THAT YOU WANTED HIM TO BE.

465
00:19:19.008 --> 00:19:21.709
YOU JUST COULDN'T SEE THAT.

466
00:19:21.777 --> 00:19:24.478
THE BOY HAD 2 CHOICES:

467
00:19:24.547 --> 00:19:27.715
TO FAIL IN FRONT
OF YOU OR TO QUIT.

468
00:19:28.651 --> 00:19:30.417
EITHER WAY. HE LOST.

469
00:19:36.141 --> 00:19:38.308
SO YOU JUST QUIT

470
00:19:38.377 --> 00:19:40.694
WITHOUT EVEN BEING MAN
ENOUGH TO OWN UP TO IT.

471
00:19:40.763 --> 00:19:42.207
THERE'S MORE TO THE STORY. DAD.

472
00:19:42.231 --> 00:19:43.508
YOU DON'T KNOW THE WHOLE STORY.

473
00:19:43.532 --> 00:19:44.993
I'VE HAD ENOUGH!

474
00:19:45.017 --> 00:19:47.298
ME. TOO. COME ON.
HALEY. I'LL TAKE YOU HOME.

475
00:19:47.353 --> 00:19:49.052
THANKS FOR DINNER.

476
00:19:49.122 --> 00:19:53.223
WELL. I CAN SHOW MYSELF
OUT. THANK YOU. MAY.

477
00:19:54.426 --> 00:19:55.526
DEB.

478
00:19:59.031 --> 00:20:00.931
HAPPY BIRTHDAY. DANNY.

479
00:20:03.669 --> 00:20:04.935
DANNY. DON'T...

480
00:20:05.004 --> 00:20:06.103
WHY?

481
00:20:12.528 --> 00:20:14.962
WELL. I GUESS
I'LL DO THE DISHES.

482
00:20:25.758 --> 00:20:28.291
ALL RIGHT. LET'S JUST
TRY TO GET SOME SLEEP.

483
00:20:28.360 --> 00:20:30.506
THEN WE'LL BE AT THE BRIDGE
AS SOON AS IT OPENS UP.

484
00:20:30.530 --> 00:20:32.229
WHAT'D HE SAY. 6:00 A.M.?

485
00:20:32.297 --> 00:20:34.197
WE'LL BE THERE AT 5:00.

486
00:20:38.838 --> 00:20:40.604
WHAT?

487
00:20:40.673 --> 00:20:43.707
I'M IN A HURRY TO FIND
OUT IF MY DAD IS DEAD.

488
00:20:44.443 --> 00:20:46.243
IT'S KIND OF SURREAL.

489
00:20:50.315 --> 00:20:52.883
YEAH. IT'S PRETTY MESSED UP.

490
00:20:52.952 --> 00:20:54.785
YOU KNOW HOW IN DREAMS.

491
00:20:54.854 --> 00:20:56.865
YOU'RE ALWAYS TRYING TO GET
TO SOMEPLACE YOU NEED TO BE

492
00:20:56.889 --> 00:20:58.634
BUT YOU NEVER REALLY GET THERE?

493
00:20:58.658 --> 00:20:59.757
YEAH.

494
00:21:05.998 --> 00:21:07.898
I WISH I COULD WAKE UP.

495
00:21:10.703 --> 00:21:13.170
MAYBE WE SHOULD
TRY TO GET SOME SLEEP.

496
00:21:13.238 --> 00:21:14.939
YOU THINK YOU CAN?

497
00:21:15.374 --> 00:21:16.614
OK.

498
00:21:20.346 --> 00:21:22.146
I'LL JUST SLEEP ON
THE FLOOR. ALL RIGHT?

499
00:21:22.214 --> 00:21:23.847
DON'T BE STUPID.

500
00:21:42.902 --> 00:21:44.451
LOOK. PEYTON.

501
00:21:46.222 --> 00:21:49.756
I JUST WISH THERE WAS
SOMETHING I COULD DO OR SAY

502
00:21:49.826 --> 00:21:52.159
TO HELP YOU THROUGH THIS.

503
00:21:52.228 --> 00:21:53.861
YOU ALREADY HAVE.

504
00:21:55.164 --> 00:21:56.663
THANKS. LUCAS.

505
00:22:06.542 --> 00:22:07.657
GOOD NIGHT.

506
00:22:07.726 --> 00:22:08.759
GOOD NIGHT.

507
00:22:20.973 --> 00:22:22.550
I'M SORRY YOU HAD TO SEE THAT.

508
00:22:22.574 --> 00:22:24.942
NO. IT'S OK.

509
00:22:25.011 --> 00:22:27.177
IT HELPED ME UNDERSTAND YOU.

510
00:22:34.954 --> 00:22:37.104
YOU KNOW. GROWING UP.

511
00:22:37.173 --> 00:22:40.741
THERE WERE CERTAIN THINGS
THAT WERE JUST CARVED IN STONE.

512
00:22:40.809 --> 00:22:43.855
AND THE MAIN ONE WAS THAT DAN
SCOTT WOULD HAVE BEEN A PRO

513
00:22:43.879 --> 00:22:46.514
IF HE DIDN'T BLOW OUT HIS KNEE.

514
00:22:46.582 --> 00:22:50.934
SO. ALL THIS TIME. HE'S JUST
BEEN FEEDING ME THIS LINE OF CRAP

515
00:22:51.003 --> 00:22:54.371
ABOUT HOW GREAT
HE WOULD HAVE BEEN.

516
00:22:54.439 --> 00:22:56.940
AND HOW I'D NEVER
BE AS GOOD AS HIM.

517
00:22:59.411 --> 00:23:00.644
BASTARD.

518
00:23:01.964 --> 00:23:04.832
AT LEAST YOU KNOW THE
TRUTH. THOUGH. RIGHT?

519
00:23:07.903 --> 00:23:10.471
I JUST DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO WITH IT.

520
00:23:11.039 --> 00:23:12.072
OK.

521
00:23:12.875 --> 00:23:13.940
GOOD NIGHT.

522
00:23:14.009 --> 00:23:15.342
GOOD NIGHT.

523
00:23:15.411 --> 00:23:16.977
I'M HERE IF YOU NEED ME. OK?

524
00:23:17.045 --> 00:23:18.412
ALL RIGHT.

525
00:23:22.351 --> 00:23:24.501
HEY. REMEMBER HOW I SAID

526
00:23:24.570 --> 00:23:28.488
MY FAMILY'S SO SCREWED UP. NOTHING
NEW WOULD MAKE A DIFFERENCE?

527
00:23:29.424 --> 00:23:30.557
YEAH.

528
00:23:31.627 --> 00:23:33.043
I WAS WRONG.

529
00:23:51.797 --> 00:23:53.125
YOU WANT TO HEAR MY SIDE OF IT?

530
00:23:53.149 --> 00:23:55.199
WHY SHOULD I BELIEVE IT?

531
00:23:55.268 --> 00:23:56.908
THIS WHOLE TIME
YOU'VE BEEN RIDING ME.

532
00:23:56.952 --> 00:23:59.536
YOU'VE KNOWN
EXACTLY THE WAY I FEEL.

533
00:23:59.605 --> 00:24:03.357
NOW THAT THAT'S IN MY HEAD. IT
JUST MAKES IT THAT MUCH WORSE.

534
00:24:07.363 --> 00:24:12.032
I WAS A GREAT PLAYER.
NATHAN. IN HIGH SCHOOL.

535
00:24:12.100 --> 00:24:15.935
BUT WHEN I GOT TO CAROLINA. I
KNEW IT WASN'T GONNA BE THE SAME.

536
00:24:18.006 --> 00:24:20.084
MY DAD COULDN'T SEE IT. THOUGH.

537
00:24:20.108 --> 00:24:22.776
IT WAS HARD ON YOUR
GRANDMOTHER. TOO.

538
00:24:22.844 --> 00:24:25.128
SO WHEN I GOT HURT.

539
00:24:25.197 --> 00:24:28.343
SHE CAME TO ME AND PLEADED
WITH ME TO WALK AWAY.

540
00:24:28.367 --> 00:24:31.167
SHE SAID IT WOULD BE
BETTER FOR ALL OF US.

541
00:24:32.538 --> 00:24:33.787
SO I DID.

542
00:24:36.325 --> 00:24:38.359
WORST DECISION OF MY LIFE.

543
00:24:40.145 --> 00:24:44.532
IT FELT GOOD TO GET OUT
FROM UNDERNEATH MY FATHER.

544
00:24:44.600 --> 00:24:48.886
AND THEN AFTER A WHILE I REALIZED
I WASN'T PLAYING FOR HIM AT ALL.

545
00:24:48.954 --> 00:24:51.488
THE GAME MEANT THE WORLD TO ME.

546
00:24:51.556 --> 00:24:55.692
I JUST NEVER TOOK THE TIME TO
STAND BACK AND REALIZE THAT.

547
00:24:55.761 --> 00:24:57.555
SO I TRIED TO GET BACK INTO IT.

548
00:24:57.579 --> 00:25:00.180
REHAB. RUNNING. WEIGHTS.

549
00:25:00.249 --> 00:25:03.750
IT WAS TOO LATE. MY
KNEE NEVER RESPONDED.

550
00:25:06.255 --> 00:25:09.290
IT WAS OVER FOR ME.

551
00:25:09.358 --> 00:25:12.843
SO YOU THINK THAT SOMEHOW GIVES
YOU THE RIGHT TO HAMMER ME ALL THE TIME?

552
00:25:12.895 --> 00:25:15.123
I KNOW I PUSH YOU. I
KNOW I'M HARD ON YOU.

553
00:25:15.147 --> 00:25:17.358
BUT I'M TRYING TO SAVE
YOU FROM A LIFE OF REGRET.

554
00:25:17.382 --> 00:25:18.894
AND TRUST ME. YOU DON'T WANT IT.

555
00:25:18.918 --> 00:25:22.386
SO THEN. YOU MAKE ME
FEEL LIKE CRAP ALL THE TIME.

556
00:25:22.454 --> 00:25:23.770
IT REALLY HELPS. DAD.

557
00:25:23.839 --> 00:25:25.171
I COULD HAVE BEEN STRONGER.

558
00:25:25.240 --> 00:25:27.001
BUT I PUSH YOU SO YOU WILL BE.

559
00:25:27.025 --> 00:25:29.137
SO THINGS WILL END UP BETTER
FOR YOU THAN THEY DID FOR ME.

560
00:25:29.161 --> 00:25:31.962
THEN YOU'RE SAFE. DAD.

561
00:25:32.031 --> 00:25:35.015
THERE'S NO WAY I'M EVER
GONNA END UP LIKE YOU.

562
00:25:55.170 --> 00:25:56.269
HEY.

563
00:25:56.739 --> 00:25:58.205
HEY.

564
00:25:58.273 --> 00:25:59.740
WHAT YOU GOT?

565
00:26:01.277 --> 00:26:04.061
"TO MY HEART. LOVE. DAD."

566
00:26:05.297 --> 00:26:07.815
HE GAVE IT TO ME
ON MY LAST BIRTHDAY.

567
00:26:10.936 --> 00:26:12.886
WHAT IF IT'S HIM. LUCAS?

568
00:26:12.955 --> 00:26:14.404
IT'S NOT GONNA BE.

569
00:26:14.473 --> 00:26:16.105
'CAUSE I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'D DO.

570
00:26:16.174 --> 00:26:17.808
IT'S GONNA BE OK.

571
00:26:19.128 --> 00:26:21.728
I JUST KEEP TRYING TO PICTURE
WALKING INTO THAT ROOM

572
00:26:21.797 --> 00:26:25.315
AND SEEING HIM LYING
THERE. BUT I HIT A WALL.

573
00:26:28.120 --> 00:26:31.889
WHY DOES IT SEEM LIKE EVERY TIME
THINGS ARE FINALLY GONNA BE OK.

574
00:26:31.957 --> 00:26:33.574
SOMETHING TERRIBLE HAPPENS?

575
00:26:33.643 --> 00:26:35.759
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT IT HAS.

576
00:26:44.619 --> 00:26:47.170
KEEP HIM CLOSE TO
YOUR HEART. PEYTON.

577
00:26:49.292 --> 00:26:51.107
GET SOME SLEEP. OK?

578
00:27:12.197 --> 00:27:15.766
YOU CAN SLEEP IN THE BEDROOM.
I'LL STAY OUT HERE TONIGHT.

579
00:27:19.237 --> 00:27:22.806
HAS IT EVER ONCE
BOTHERED YOUR CONSCIENCE

580
00:27:22.875 --> 00:27:27.427
THAT OUR ENTIRE RELATIONSHIP
IS BASED ON YOUR LIE?

581
00:27:27.496 --> 00:27:30.397
THAT WHEN YOU WERE
FORCED TO WALK AWAY

582
00:27:30.466 --> 00:27:34.384
BECAUSE OF YOUR SO-CALLED
INJURY. I DROPPED OUT. TOO.

583
00:27:34.453 --> 00:27:36.286
WE BOTH DROPPED
OUT TO RAISE NATHAN.

584
00:27:36.354 --> 00:27:38.021
DON'T REWRITE HISTORY.

585
00:27:38.073 --> 00:27:41.241
OH. SO YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO CAN PLAY THAT GAME?

586
00:27:41.309 --> 00:27:44.755
I THOUGHT I KNEW THE MAN I WAS
CHOOSING TO SPEND MY LIFE WITH.

587
00:27:44.779 --> 00:27:47.764
THE INJURY WAS REAL. DEB.

588
00:27:47.833 --> 00:27:51.334
AND. YES. I DECIDED
NOT TO REHAB IT AT FIRST.

589
00:27:51.403 --> 00:27:54.471
BY THE TIME I CHANGED
MY MIND. IT WAS TOO LATE.

590
00:27:54.540 --> 00:27:58.392
I DID IT IN SERVICE
OF YOU AND NATHAN.

591
00:27:58.460 --> 00:28:02.378
NOW. I KNOW HOW YOU'D HOLD IT
AGAINST ME FOR NOT TELLING YOU.

592
00:28:02.447 --> 00:28:05.799
BUT DID YOU EVER
THINK THAT MAYBE I DID IT

593
00:28:05.868 --> 00:28:07.985
TO PROTECT YOU FROM IT ALL?

594
00:28:10.522 --> 00:28:12.751
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU
NEED TO BELIEVE.

595
00:28:12.775 --> 00:28:14.341
IT'S THE TRUTH.

596
00:28:15.677 --> 00:28:17.043
THE TRUTH?

597
00:28:18.013 --> 00:28:19.562
IN THIS HOUSE?

598
00:28:43.539 --> 00:28:45.004
WHAT'S ALL THIS?

599
00:28:45.074 --> 00:28:46.156
OH.

600
00:28:46.225 --> 00:28:48.402
SORRY. I DIDN'T
MEAN TO WAKE YOU.

601
00:28:48.426 --> 00:28:50.360
I WASN'T ASLEEP.

602
00:28:50.428 --> 00:28:52.762
I HIT THE VENDING MACHINES.

603
00:28:52.831 --> 00:28:54.063
HUNGRY?

604
00:28:55.734 --> 00:28:58.635
I THOUGHT YOU SHOULD
PROBABLY EAT SOMETHING.

605
00:29:02.774 --> 00:29:05.242
AFTER MY MOM DIED. UM.

606
00:29:05.310 --> 00:29:07.677
MY DAD COULDN'T COOK.

607
00:29:07.746 --> 00:29:11.648
SO WE LIVED ON FROZEN
PIZZAS FOR THE LONGEST TIME.

608
00:29:12.851 --> 00:29:14.851
I COULD LIVE ON PIZZA.

609
00:29:14.920 --> 00:29:16.553
HE'D. UH.

610
00:29:16.622 --> 00:29:20.156
HE'D BUY THESE CHEESE PIZZAS AND
THEN HE'D PUT HIS OWN TOPPINGS ON.

611
00:29:20.225 --> 00:29:23.526
PICKLES. BOLOGNA.
PINEAPPLE. WHATEVER.

612
00:29:23.595 --> 00:29:24.895
THAT'S NASTY.

613
00:29:24.964 --> 00:29:27.514
NO. ACTUALLY. THEY
WERE REALLY GOOD.

614
00:29:29.201 --> 00:29:32.552
I THINK HE DID IT MOSTLY
JUST TO MAKE ME LAUGH.

615
00:29:32.621 --> 00:29:35.888
YOU KNOW. TO HELP ME
FORGET FOR A LITTLE BIT.

616
00:29:46.101 --> 00:29:47.434
YOU READY?

617
00:29:49.254 --> 00:29:50.269
NO.

618
00:29:54.960 --> 00:29:56.226
LET'S GO.

619
00:30:13.779 --> 00:30:14.945
MORNING.

620
00:30:15.013 --> 00:30:16.780
MORNING.

621
00:30:16.849 --> 00:30:19.483
SCRAMBLED OR FRIED?
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

622
00:30:19.551 --> 00:30:23.252
I THINK NOBODY'S
GONNA BE THAT HUNGRY.

623
00:30:23.321 --> 00:30:26.957
I'M GLAD YOU STOOD UP TO
ROYAL THE WAY YOU DID. DEB.

624
00:30:27.025 --> 00:30:29.626
I DIDN'T MEAN TO HURT DAN.

625
00:30:29.695 --> 00:30:32.596
BUT THIS LYING OVER THE
YEARS HAS GOTTEN SO TIRESOME.

626
00:30:32.664 --> 00:30:35.765
I DID WHAT I THOUGHT I
HAD TO DO TO SAVE MY SON.

627
00:30:36.468 --> 00:30:38.134
THAT'S WHAT WE DO.

628
00:30:39.104 --> 00:30:40.971
I'M GLAD YOU SPOKE UP.

629
00:30:43.842 --> 00:30:45.082
DAN?

630
00:30:47.012 --> 00:30:51.648
SON. YOU KNOW. SOMEDAY YOU'RE
GONNA REALIZE I DID YOU A FAVOR.

631
00:30:51.717 --> 00:30:54.651
YOUR DADDY'S GONNA
GET OVER THIS EVENTUALLY.

632
00:30:54.720 --> 00:30:58.171
BUT IF YOU LET HISTORY REPEAT
ITSELF. YOUR SON MAY NOT.

633
00:30:59.324 --> 00:31:01.091
I'M GOING FOR A RUN.

634
00:31:04.196 --> 00:31:06.946
OH. WELL. I THINK I'LL
SCRAMBLE THE EGGS.

635
00:31:07.015 --> 00:31:08.148
YEAH.

636
00:31:13.389 --> 00:31:15.155
LISTEN. NATHAN. I...

637
00:31:17.125 --> 00:31:19.565
WHATEVER YOU'RE GOING THROUGH.

638
00:31:22.130 --> 00:31:24.814
I'M SORRY ABOUT YOUR DAD.

639
00:31:24.883 --> 00:31:27.367
I UNDERSTAND WHY
HE DID IT. GRANDPA.

640
00:31:29.538 --> 00:31:32.505
HE MUST HAVE REALLY
LOVED YOU. YOU KNOW THAT?

641
00:31:32.574 --> 00:31:36.008
BECAUSE ANYTHING SEEMED
BETTER THAN DISAPPOINTING YOU.

642
00:32:02.087 --> 00:32:03.553
IT'S NOT HIM.

643
00:32:14.416 --> 00:32:15.982
YOU DID GOOD.

644
00:32:16.051 --> 00:32:18.718
I FELT LIKE MY CHEST
WAS GONNA EXPLODE.

645
00:32:27.112 --> 00:32:28.244
PEYTON'S PLACE.

646
00:32:28.314 --> 00:32:29.680
<i>HEY. IT'S ME.</i>

647
00:32:29.748 --> 00:32:31.442
HEY. I WAS JUST DIALING
YOU. THAT'S FREAKY.

648
00:32:31.466 --> 00:32:32.999
WELL. IT'S GOOD NEWS.

649
00:32:33.067 --> 00:32:35.279
YEAH. I KNOW. I JUST GOT OFF
THE PHONE WITH THE COAST GUARD.

650
00:32:35.303 --> 00:32:37.270
THEY MADE CONTACT
WITH HIS BOAT. HE'S FINE.

651
00:32:38.540 --> 00:32:40.051
THEY FOUND YOUR DAD. HE'S OK.

652
00:32:40.075 --> 00:32:41.141
OH.

653
00:32:43.979 --> 00:32:45.557
ALL RIGHT. WE'RE HEADED HOME.

654
00:32:45.581 --> 00:32:46.763
OK. I'M WAITING.

655
00:32:46.832 --> 00:32:48.009
<i>LOVE YOU.</i>

656
00:32:48.033 --> 00:32:49.199
LOVE YOU. TOO. BYE.

657
00:32:49.267 --> 00:32:50.900
MY GOD. THAT'S...

658
00:32:51.470 --> 00:32:52.470
WAIT.

659
00:32:52.538 --> 00:32:53.470
WHAT?

660
00:32:53.539 --> 00:32:54.771
UM.

661
00:32:54.840 --> 00:32:56.172
MY BRACELET.

662
00:32:56.241 --> 00:32:57.974
I MUST HAVE LEFT
IT IN THE MOTEL.

663
00:32:58.043 --> 00:32:59.459
ALL RIGHT. LET'S GO.

664
00:33:02.181 --> 00:33:03.246
HEY.

665
00:33:03.315 --> 00:33:04.359
HEY.

666
00:33:04.383 --> 00:33:05.615
GRANDMA'S MAKING BREAKFAST.

667
00:33:05.684 --> 00:33:07.917
SHOW STARTS AT 9:00. YOU IN?

668
00:33:07.986 --> 00:33:09.352
UM.

669
00:33:09.421 --> 00:33:12.255
AS FUN AS LAST NIGHT
WAS. I THINK I'M GONNA PASS.

670
00:33:13.892 --> 00:33:16.576
YOU KNOW. I'VE BEEN THINKING.

671
00:33:17.912 --> 00:33:20.747
NOW THAT YOU KNOW THE
TRUTH ABOUT YOUR DAD.

672
00:33:20.815 --> 00:33:23.183
YOU'RE FREE. RIGHT? I MEAN...

673
00:33:23.251 --> 00:33:25.196
HE'S BEEN LYING TO
YOU ALL THIS TIME.

674
00:33:25.220 --> 00:33:27.501
YOU DON'T HAVE TO
LISTEN TO HIM ANYMORE.

675
00:33:27.555 --> 00:33:29.722
THERE'S NO MORE PRESSURE.

676
00:33:29.791 --> 00:33:31.958
YEAH. I WISH THAT WERE TRUE.

677
00:33:32.961 --> 00:33:35.061
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

678
00:33:36.899 --> 00:33:38.631
MY DAD WALKED AWAY.

679
00:33:38.700 --> 00:33:41.634
AND HIS FATHER WILL
NEVER FORGIVE HIM FOR THAT.

680
00:33:41.703 --> 00:33:42.752
I HAVE TO GO BACK.

681
00:33:42.820 --> 00:33:43.820
NATHAN...

682
00:33:43.889 --> 00:33:45.938
I HAVE TO BEAT HIM. HALEY.

683
00:33:47.809 --> 00:33:51.010
IT'S THE ONLY WAY I'M EVER
GONNA BE FREE OF MY DAD.

684
00:33:58.103 --> 00:33:59.903
IT HAS TO BE IN HERE.

685
00:34:07.095 --> 00:34:08.335
GOT IT?

686
00:34:12.217 --> 00:34:13.500
IT'S OK.

687
00:34:13.568 --> 00:34:15.568
EVERYTHING'S OK NOW. OK?

688
00:34:25.764 --> 00:34:29.282
<i>♪</i>

689
00:34:29.351 --> 00:34:32.085
<i>♪ I'VE BEEN DOWN AND
I'M WONDERING WHY ♪</i>

690
00:34:32.153 --> 00:34:34.954
<i>♪ THESE LITTLE BLACK CLOUDS
KEEP WALKING AROUND ♪</i>

691
00:34:35.023 --> 00:34:36.389
<i>♪ WITH ME ♪</i>

692
